        <p>Not only can you select a certain page layout to display a<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> topic</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> document</MadCap:conditionalText> in the XML Editor, but you can also choose a specific page type within that layout. This can be especially useful when you know for certain that a particular<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> topic</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> document</MadCap:conditionalText> will display on the first page of a chapter, a left page, a right page, etc. The reason <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> does not automatically show a<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> topic</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> document</MadCap:conditionalText> in the appropriate page type is because it won't assign page types to content until you generate the output. However, sometimes you may know in advance which page type will be used<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> because of its placement in the outline TOC</MadCap:conditionalText>, so you can choose any page type contained in the layout to display the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> topic</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor"> document</MadCap:conditionalText> in the XML&#160;Editor.</p>
